        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:46AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 645 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Weinert, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Weinert, O'Brien, Irby, and Us-277 Near The Haskell-Knox County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
